# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# Python bytecode & cache files
#
# SETUP (run once):
# 1. Create this file in the project root: .gitignore
# 2. Add the ignore rules below
# 3. Stage and commit it:
#      git add .gitignore
#      git commit -m "chore(gitignore): ignore Python cache files"
#
# Python automatically generates __pycache__/ directories and
# *.pyc/*.pyo/*.pyd bytecode files at runtime. These files are
# platform- and version-specific, regenerated as needed, and should
# never be committed to version control.
#
# The ignore patterns below apply recursively to the entire repository,
# meaning any matching files or directories in any subfolder are
# ignored.
#
# IMPORTANT:
# .gitignore does NOT remove files that are already tracked.
# If Python cache files were committed before this file was added,
# remove them from Git *after* adding this .gitignore using:
#
#   git rm -r --cached __pycache__
#   git rm --cached *.pyc *.pyo *.pyd
#
# Then commit the cleanup:
#   git commit -m "chore(gitignore): remove tracked Python cache files"
#
# Sanity check (after pushing)
#   git status
#   git status --ignored
# --------------------------------------------------------------------

